{"id":14881536,"mediaExerciseId":"909289b6-c9c8-4a96-8c62-95f8cf73c662","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"16","chapterTitle":"Financial Leverage and Capital Structure Policy","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"16.5","sectionTitle":"Bankruptcy Costs","pageNumber":552,"solutions":[{"id":5991943,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"$a)$ Direct bankruptcy costs are those expenses that are directly attributable to a company's bankruptcy filing, such expenses are incurred throughout the bankruptcy process, when a business decides to declare bankruptcy, it must pay administrative and legal fees, which also are referred to as direct bankruptcy costs.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2221bf8e9498f457b8ef152b92742020/cbd7c2176f191e082fb1ffe4539639e7/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2221bf8e9498f457b8ef152b92742020/cbd7c2176f191e082fb1ffe4539639e7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"$b)$ Indirect bankruptcy expenses are the cost incurred by a company to prevent declaring bankruptcy, when a corporation is in a financial crisis and therefore can afford the extra costs of a bankruptcy case, it may seek to prevent it, indirect bankruptcy costs will be incurred as a condition of doing so.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":175,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2221bf8e9498f457b8ef152b92742020/6f8960bbd64e7c183fa1e924b3ddb31d/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":88,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/2221bf8e9498f457b8ef152b92742020/6f8960bbd64e7c183fa1e924b3ddb31d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solut